Let me clear my mind of all resentment, anger and hatred. Let me banish all want and need and agitation. Let my mind be bright and awake (sati) . Let it be filled with friendly feeling. (piti)

Let the clear mind experience clear dharma (Dhamma Vicaya) . Let my mind be filled with compassion. Let me find peace and joy and give them to everybody.(Passaddhi) Let me have metta so I can feel other people suffering and my own joy. Let me have strength to practice without difficulties.(Viriya)

I want to keep my mind alert throughout this session. I want to attain deep concentration. I want to understand the Dharma so that I can share my understanding of Dharma with everyone. I don't have an ulterior motive. I do it for myself and everyone else. We all benefit. I want my mind to be clear. I want everyone's mind to be clear. I want to find peace and joy for myself and everyone everywhere. I am doing this for myself and everyone.

I am clearing my mind to taste the peace and joy that lies down at the roots of my mind, below the thoughts. I want peace and joy for myself and everyone.(piti) I want to see impermanence happening before the eye of wisdom, so that I can be free and help everyone else become free too!

